adviseScripts.text: Snow White closes her eyes and recalls the past, which has become a blur.
She concentrates on polishing her weapon.
What's this? A new toy?
Cool weapon.
It's not a toy!
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Go away, Commander!
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Huh...?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: How did you know?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Yeah, it's a modified...
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: What's that other thing beside you? Some kind of toy?
Oh, this?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: It's a pistol, not a toy!
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: If you've come here just to tease me again, you can leave.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: *Bang*
I guess people are right when they say teens are temperamental.
Snow White closes her eyes and recalls the past, which has become a blur.
Commander,
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: how can I become as strong as Lilith?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: That's something you must figure out for yourself.
Have you not gotten enough sleep or something?
Oh, okay...
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I see.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I'll try my best.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: There you go again, treating me like a child!
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: You just wait and see,
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I'll become stronger for sure!
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Snow White storms off into her room and spends some time alone thinking.
Snow White closes her eyes and recalls the past, which has become a blur.
Commander...
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Yes?
What are you eating?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Oh, this?
Share snack with Snow White.
Pretend to share snack with Snow White.
Have some.
Thanks!
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: *Munch munch*
It's delicious!
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Here.
Thanks.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: *Yoink*
Huh...?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: After feigning that I'm going to share my snack with Snow White, I proceed to yank it back and eat it myself.
Ah, delicious.
After getting the snack, Snow White goes back to her room happily.
Snow White closes her eyes and recalls the past, which has become a blur.
Commander,
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: why does Red Hood always make fun of me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Because you're so cute.
Because she considers you a good friend.
That's just a nice way of saying she considers me a child, isn't it?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: How did you know?
How could I not? It's so obvious.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I see.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: She's always pranking me because she's fond of me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Thanks for letting me know, Commander.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Snow White turns to head back to her room, and is promptly put into a headlock by Red Hood.
Snow White closes her eyes and recalls the past, which has become a blur.
Commander, Red Hood told me the nudie mag she has
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: was a gift from you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Is that true?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Not at all.
Yes, it's true.
I knew it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: You wouldn't be caught dead with that kind of reading material.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I'm glad my hunch was correct.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: For real?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Just kidding. She's lying.
I knew it!
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: What a relief.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Snow White returns to her room, thoroughly reassured.
Snow White closes her eyes and recalls the past, which has become a blur.
Scarlet's sword is amazing.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Sometimes, it looks as though it has a life of its own.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: You didn't know? It is alive.
Perhaps because she wields it with such passion.
"Gee willikers, no kidding!"
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: ...Is that what you expected me to say?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I'm not as gullible as you think, Commander.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Right...
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I think Scarlet said something like that before.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: It's a good thing I asked you, hehe.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Thanks.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: After returning to her room, Snow White decides to delve seriously into swords again.
Snow White closes her eyes and recalls the past, which has become a blur.
Dorothy always seems hard to approach.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Do you get the same feeling, Commander?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Yeah, she can be a bit standoffish.
Hmm...is she? I've never felt anything like that.
I wouldn't go as far as saying "standoffish", but...
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: How should I put it...
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: She's a bit like you when you get upset.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: ... Right, I nearly forgot.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: You can make friends with everyone so easily.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I suppose that would make you approachable.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Why does it feel like there's a hidden meaning there...
Even after Snow White returns to her room, she continues to think about Dorothy's temperament.
Snow White closes her eyes and recalls the past, which has become a blur.
Rapunzel has been acting a little strange lately.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: She'll breathe all heavily, and her face turns beet red.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: What's going on with her?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I think she's gotten addicted to that nudie mag.
She's attempting mightily to be reborn as a true saint, so she needs all the help you can give her.
I can't believe she'd become addicted to such smut!
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Could it be because of Red Hood?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: A true saint?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: ... Wow, amazing.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: So that's what you have to go through to achieve sainthood?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: In the end, Snow White doesn't get a satisfactory answer.
Snow White closes her eyes and recalls the past, which has become a blur.
I want to become as mature as Lilith.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: That way, I'll be able to get back at Red Hood whenever she teases me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I don't think being mature has anything to do with it.
Sorry to tell you, but I don't think it's possible for you to ever become like Lilith.
You think so?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Oh, I get it!
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: You're saying I can get back at Red Hood whenever I want!
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Hehe, thanks, Commander!
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I'll think of something.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: You didn't have to rub it in my face, you know.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: You're worse than Red Hood sometimes.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Snow White storms off, leaving me behind, slightly hurt and bewildered.
Snow White closes her eyes and recalls the past, which has become a blur.
Ugh, Commander.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Could you please have a word with Scarlet and Dorothy?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: They had another squabble today and made a total mess of the barracks.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Okay, but just one word, no more.
Okay, I'll tell them to behave.
You don't have to look at me like you want to squash me under your bootheel...
Wow...
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: What?
Uh... Nothing. Thanks.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: It's just that I thought you'd brush me off again, but you didn't.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Snow White hurries back to her room.
Snow White closes her eyes and recalls the past, which has become a blur.
If there's any kind of weapon that you need,
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: just let me know,
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: and I can make it for you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I don't need anything as long as I have you protecting me.
It's okay, what I have right now suits me just fine.
Well, of course I'll always protect you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: But I may not always be around,
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: so all the same, feel free to tell me if you need anything crafted.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I've had a look at your current loadout,
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: and it's seen better days.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: You really should let me craft a new one for you,
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: or at least let me refurbish your current arsenal.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Is that okay?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: After some quibbling back and forth, I finally relent, and Snow White leaves content with the outcome.
Snow White closes her eyes and recalls the past, which has become a blur.
What do you usually do when you've got some time to rest, Commander?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I take a rest, literally.
Take a guess.
Makes sense.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Sufficient rest is imperative for a healthy body and mind.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Exactly, so you should go to bed at a reasonable hour instead of staying up all night polishing your weapon.
How did you know?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Hmm... I think you...
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Meditate?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: That's correct.
You're not just saying that, are you?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Snow White goes back early to rest.
Snow White closes her eyes and recalls the past, which has become a blur.
If we reclaim the surface,
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: what do you intend to do there?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: To be honest, I've never given it much thought.
I suppose I'd go on an outing with all of you.
I thought that might be the case.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Do you have any suggestions?
I want to go on a trip.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: With everyone else, I mean.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: You mean like a trip?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: That'd be nice.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I'd love to go with you!
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Back in her room, Snow White daydreams of reclaiming the surface.
Snow White closes her eyes and recalls the past, which has become a blur.
Commander, do you cherish old stuff of yours more?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: They do have their own unique charm.
No, I have no attachment to old things.
Red Hood said the same thing.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: You two really do have a lot in common,
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: even down to the fact that you both talk super loudly.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Oh, that's surprising.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I thought for sure that you'd say you did.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Our conversation is interrupted by Lilith, who comes in to notify us about mealtime.
Snow White closes her eyes and recalls the past, which has become a blur.
Why don't Scarlet and Dorothy get along?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: They're always at each others' throats whenever they're in the same room.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Maybe they were enemies in a past life.
Maybe that's just their way of showing affection.
... Do Nikkes have past lives, too?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I think so... maybe?
You just made that up, didn't you?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Ugh. Why do I even bother?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I don't know about that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Some of their fights have gotten so bad that I was worried one of them might end up dead.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: But still, they are squadmates. Maybe you're right.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Later that day, Snow White once again spends time breaking up yet another altercation between Scarlet and Dorothy.
Snow White closes her eyes and recalls the past, which has become a blur.
Commander, what kind of weather do you prefer?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Sunny or cloudy?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Neither.
I actually prefer snowy days.
Huh?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: So what do you like?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: It's a secret.
Aw, come on! That's not nice.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: So your favorite weather involves snow? How unique...
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Wait...
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Why are you staring at me like that?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: What is it?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: That night, for some reason, Snow White finds herself unable to sleep.
Snow White closes her eyes and recalls the past, which has become a blur.
Sometimes I have nightmares at night.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I dream that everyone has disappeared and I've been left all alone.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: How about I sleep next to you tonight?
It's all just a dream, nothing more.
W-what are you saying?!
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: That won't be necessary.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Sorry, but can we take a small break?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I know that,
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: but they were so vivid...it all felt so real.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Fortunately, they only last for a while.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Anyway, I'm going to take a short break.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Snow White falls asleep almost immediately.
Snow White closes her eyes and recalls the past, which has become a blur.
Hello, Commander.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Snow White is holding a steaming potato.
Would you like to share this potato?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I'm good. It's all yours.
Okay then, just a little bite.
Hehe, thanks.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: I'm famished. I could eat several of these.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Okay, here you go.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: *Chomp*
Hey, you call that a bite?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: You nearly ate the whole thing!
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Give it back!
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Snow White, still hungry, sets out to forage for other food.
Snow White closes her eyes and recalls the past, which has become a blur.
She is sleeping.
Wake her up by poking her cheek.
Wake her up by tickling her nose.
*Poke*
Mmm...
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: *Poke poke*
Mmm...
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Oh jeez, I must have fallen asleep while polishing my weapons.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Thanks for waking me up, Commander.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: *Tickle*
Mmm...
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: *Tickle tickle*
Achoo!
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: ... Hmm? Commander?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Is it raining outside?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Why are you so wet?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Snow White goes back to her room and sleeps soundly that night.
Snow White closes her eyes and recalls the past, which has become a blur.
Do you have any hobbies, Commander?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Or something that you enjoy doing?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Kind of like me with crafting weapons.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Honestly, I'm a big fan of times like these. What we're doing right now.
Nothing in particular, I'm afraid.
Really?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Me too. Well, at least I certainly don't find it unpleasant...
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Times like these, that is.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Same old answer.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Anyway, would you like some mints?
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: You yelled a whole bunch during the meeting earlier.
adviseScripts.speaker: Snow White

adviseScripts.text: Snow White proceeds to have an ordinary day like any other.
